div.p:
If you understand, all things are of one family;

if you do not understand, ten thousand distinctions and a thousand differences.

If you do not understand, all things are of one family;

if you understand, ten thousand distinctions and a thousand differences.

Old Dongshan had realized a bit of clam-and-oyster Zen;

as soon as the two shells opened, liver and entrails were exposed.

Even so, tell me, where do you see Dongshan?
